#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.43"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.43:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.43:0.2"
msgid "5. Papātavagga"
msgstr "5. A Cliff"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 43. Mahāpariḷāhasutta → pariḷāhasuttaṃ (bj) | pariḷāho (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.43:0.3"
msgid "43. Mahāpariḷāhasutta"
msgstr "43. The Intense Fever"

# BB has “conflagration”. Woodward has “great distress”. I don’t understand either of these choices. What’s wrong with “fever”, which is what the word means?
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.451"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.43:1.1"
msgid "“Atthi, bhikkhave, mahāpariḷāho nāma nirayo."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there is a hell called ‘The Intense Fever’."

msgctxt "sn56.43:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tattha yaṃ kiñci cakkhunā rūpaṃ passati, aniṭṭharūpaññeva passati no "
"iṭṭharūpaṃ; akantarūpaññeva passati no kantarūpaṃ; amanāparūpaññeva passati "
"no manāparūpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"There, whatever sight you see with your eye is unlikable, not likable; "
"undesirable, not desirable; unpleasant, not pleasant."

msgctxt "sn56.43:1.3"
msgid "Yaṃ kiñci sotena saddaṃ suṇāti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Whatever sound you hear … Whatever odor you smell … Whatever flavor you "
"taste …"

msgctxt "sn56.43:1.4"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusati … pe …"
msgstr "Whatever touch you feel …"

msgctxt "sn56.43:1.5"
msgid ""
"yaṃ kiñci manasā dhammaṃ vijānāti, aniṭṭharūpaññeva vijānāti no iṭṭharūpaṃ; "
"akantarūpaññeva vijānāti no kantarūpaṃ; amanāparūpaññeva vijānāti no "
"manāparūpan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Whatever thought you know with your mind is unlikable, not likable; "
"undesirable, not desirable; unpleasant, not pleasant.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.43:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, one of the mendicants said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn56.43:2.2"
msgid "“mahā vata so, bhante, pariḷāho, sumahā vata so, bhante, pariḷāho."
msgstr "“Sir, that fever really is intense, so very intense."

msgctxt "sn56.43:2.3"
msgid ""
"Atthi nu kho, bhante, etamhā pariḷāhā añño pariḷāho mahantataro ceva "
"bhayānakataro cā”ti?"
msgstr "Is there any other fever more intense and scarier than this one?”"

msgctxt "sn56.43:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Atthi kho, bhikkhu, etamhā pariḷāhā añño pariḷāho mahantataro ca "
"bhayānakataro cā”ti."
msgstr "“There is, mendicant.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.43:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamo pana, bhante, etamhā pariḷāhā añño pariḷāho mahantataro ca "
"bhayānakataro cā”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, what is it?”"

msgctxt "sn56.43:3.2"
msgid ""
"“Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"nappajānanti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are ascetics and brahmins who don’t truly understand "
"about suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path."

msgctxt "sn56.43:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti, te "
"jātisaṃvattanikesu saṅkhāresu abhiramanti … pe …"
msgstr "They take pleasure in choices that lead to rebirth …"

msgctxt "sn56.43:3.4"
msgid "abhiratā … pe … abhisaṅkharonti … pe …"
msgstr "They continue to make such choices …"

msgctxt "sn56.43:3.5"
msgid ""
"abhisaṅkharitvā jātipariḷāhenapi pariḍayhanti, jarāpariḷāhenapi "
"pariḍayhanti, maraṇapariḷāhenapi pariḍayhanti, "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsapariḷāhenapi pariḍayhanti."
msgstr ""
"Having made such choices, they burn with the fever of rebirth, old age, and "
"death, of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn56.43:3.6"
msgid ""
"Te na parimuccanti jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi "
"domanassehi upāyāsehi."
msgstr ""
"They’re not freed from rebirth, old age, and death, from sorrow, "
"lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn56.43:3.7"
msgid "‘Na parimuccanti dukkhasmā’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "They’re not freed from suffering, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.452"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.43:4.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti."
msgstr ""
"There are ascetics and brahmins who truly understand about suffering, its "
"origin, its cessation, and the path."

msgctxt "sn56.43:4.2"
msgid "Te jātisaṃvattanikesu saṅkhāresu nābhiramanti … pe …"
msgstr "They don’t take pleasure in choices that lead to rebirth …"

msgctxt "sn56.43:4.3"
msgid "anabhiratā … pe … nābhisaṅkharonti … pe …"
msgstr "They stop making such choices …"

msgctxt "sn56.43:4.4"
msgid ""
"anabhisaṅkharitvā jātipariḷāhenapi na pariḍayhanti, jarāpariḷāhenapi na "
"pariḍayhanti, maraṇapariḷāhenapi na pariḍayhanti, "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsapariḷāhenapi na pariḍayhanti."
msgstr ""
"Having stopped making such choices, they don’t burn with the fever of "
"rebirth, old age, and death, of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and "
"distress."

msgctxt "sn56.43:4.5"
msgid ""
"Te parimuccanti jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi "
"domanassehi upāyāsehi."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from rebirth, old age, and death, from sorrow, lamentation, "
"pain, sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn56.43:4.6"
msgid "‘Parimuccanti dukkhasmā’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "They’re freed from suffering, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.43:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.43:5.2"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
